
 stripecart  (under development)
 ___
 
 open-source shopping cart for simplified commerce using stripe.com payments

 requires:

 •  existing MySQL database
 •  SSL Cert for use in connecting to stripe.com
 •  minimum 640x400 px area in your page layout
 •  3 PHP-writable folders on webserver 
     (config file, new pages, new images)

 built upon:
 
 Linux, Apache, MySQL InnoDB, PHP [with cURL, gd, mail, file_upload]
 HTML5, CSS3, jQuery +UI, SynapticData pseudoAjax CMS, tinymce, tinymce_img,
 Ben Alman's BBQ, webtoolkit jQuery base64, Jeff Todnem's passwordmeter.js,
 Google ReCaptcha, Malsup.com jQuery Form, SynapticData Core & Acct libraries,
 Tim Eckel fastimagecopyresampled, Google WebFonts, and more.
 
 installs as widget:

 •  upload folder to your webserver
 •  write 3 lines in your webpage

 automatic installation script on first launch
 
 awesome sauce
 ___

 greg kendall, Synaptic Data Systems, Inc. - Feb 29, 2012
 dev@stripecart.com
